title: Acting SFH on food safety
content_text:
p>
    Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the Acting 
    Secretary for Food and Health, Professor Gabriel Leung, at a media stand-up 
    session in the Legislative Council Building today (May 19): Reporter: (about the shellfish poisoning cases) Acting Secretary for Food and Health: I understand that this issue of 
    paralytic shellfish poisoning is of concern to the public and of course it 
    also concerns me personally and us as the Food and Health Bureau very much.

also concerns me personally and us as the Food and Health Bureau very much. 
    Through our executive agency, the Centre for Health Protection, we are 
    closely following up on both the public health effects after consumption of 
    these shellfish products as well as trying to identify the source of these 
    shellfish products. The important thing to bear in mind is that you can rest 
    assured that we will closely follow up both through our laboratories, in 
    term of testing other products on the markets, and we are currently doing

term of testing other products on the markets, and we are currently doing 
    the tests, and as soon as we have results, we will publicise them. We are 
    making sure that each and every case of report that we get, and since 
    yesterday we have received one further report as of noon time today that is 
    suspected to be linked to the issue of current shellfish poisoning. So, both 
    for public health on the human side as well as identifying the food safety

for public health on the human side as well as identifying the food safety 
    angle, we are doing everything we can to follow this up. With the Food 
    Safety Bill in the future which we will be tabling for the Legislative 
    Council's consideration before the end of this legislative year, we would
